Abstract = {Recent advances in smartphones and affordable open-source hardware
   platforms have enabled the development of low-cost architectures for
   Internet-of-Things (IoT)-enabled home automation and security systems.
   These systems usually consist of sensing and actuating layer that is
   made up of sensors such as passive infrared sensors, also known as
   motion sensors; temperature sensors; smoke sensors, and web cameras for
   security surveillance. These sensors, smart electrical appliances, and
   other IoT devices connect to the Internet through a home gateway. This
   paper lays out an architecture for a cost-effective smart door sensor
   that will inform a user through an Android application, of door open
   events in a house or office environment. The proposed architecture uses
